          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Hedge funds bullish on gasoline</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-16-1.png" alt="Hedge funds bullish on gasoline" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Hedge funds are <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/12/13/hedge-funds-turn-more-bullish-on-gasoline/" target="_blank">betting</a> big on gasoline futures as low prices create buying opportunities. Speculators increased their net-long positions to the highest level in eight months, with inventories slipping to three-year seasonal lows. Upcoming refinery closures, like LyondellBasell's 264,000 barrels-a-day Houston plant, could tighten supply in 2024. Currently, gasoline futures sit at $1.99 per gallon, down 5% this year. </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
