              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Blackstone’s big bet</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-16-2.png" alt="Blackstone’s big bet" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);">
         Blackstone has <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/12/13/blackstone-buys-czech-warehouse-owner-ct-real-estate-from-tpg/" target="_blank">acquired</a> ten logistics parks in the Czech Republic for $495 million, reinforcing its focus on warehouses. These properties span 500,000 square meters and are located in and around the cities of Czech Republic. This acquisition comes after the €5 billion investment Blackstone made in European logistics this year. This deal is part of Blackstone's larger strategy, with logistics now accounting for 60% of its European property portfolio. The firm bets that the rents will continue to grow and deploy capital into this sector amid interest-rate shock. In September, Blackstone completed its largest European logistics transaction of €1 billion by acquiring a majority stake in Burstone Group.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
